originalText.text:
I made an appointment on Zocdoc, came half an hour earlier to the place, rang the bell many times, called many times, emailed the psychologist Courtney, she never responded, I waited for 10min, then left.

Courtney explained later thru email that she silenced her phone to she can focus on her patients, she kind of meant it's my fault that I came so early?

…well, that's good to focus on your patients, but why don't you hire someone as a front desk? Why don't you hire someone to open the door for your patient who have been waiting 10min outside on a rainy day? Why didn't you tell your patient to ring the 2nd floor doorbell when they come as there's no sign outside showing this is the right place…

Customer service is terrible!!!
